===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mrəŋ||fly; bee}}. Compare {{och-l|虻|tr=mˁraŋ|horsefly}}, {{cog|bo|སྦྲང་བུ|'''སྦྲང'''་བུ|bee}}, {{cog|sit-jap|ɣʑo||bee}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}; {{zh-ref|Benedict, 1972}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai, 2019}}).

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} reconstructs "minimal" Old Chinese ''*ləŋ'' or ''*jəŋ'': 
*''*ləŋ'' can result from the sound law ''*l-'' < ''*ml-'' < ''*m-r-'' proposed by {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2014)}} and is compatible with the fact that this word is in the {{m|zh|tr=-|黽}} phonetic series, as well as with the Min reflexes.
*''*jəŋ'' instead is potentially comparable to {{cog|my|ယင်||fly}}, {{cog|cdm|याङ्‌||insect; fly}}, yet this reconstruction and its etymology cannot be maintained due to its incompatibility with aforesaid internal Chinese evidence.
